               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism by Khvajah Ahrar, 2 items (a-b)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Summary: Collection of two works on or by the Naqshbandi Sufi, Khvājah Aḥrār. Volume not dated; item a dated 15 Ramaz̤ān 1059/22 September 1649; later replacements. Careful scribal nastaʿlīq, with shikastah āmīz and Indian taʿlīq. Annotations and corrections in margins. Stamped and Persian foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding damaged (tooled reddish brown leather exterior embellished with medallions, fine combed marbled paper pasted in two layers as doublures). Folios unbound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs; text damaged by stains and smudging. Condition fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1010-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="50r">ff. 1v-50r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of the dicta or fiqarāt ascribed to the Ṣūfī saint, Khvājah ʿUbayd Allāh Aḥrār (d. circa 895/1490). 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 50r): completed at Akbarābād (Agra), Wednesday, 15 Ramaz̤ān 1059/22 September 1649. 
</p>
                        <p>Careful scribal nastaʿlīq. Folio 1 is a replacement by a later hand in rough Indian taʿlīq, similar to that found in item b. 
</p>
                        <p>Interlinear annotations and corrections as well as in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Two letters of Khvājah ʿAbd al-Bāqī reproduced on folio 50v. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658478.0x000001 viaf_485149294387580522619"> Aḥrār, ʿUbayd Allāh ibn Maḥmūd, 1403 or 1404-1489 or 1490</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658478.0x000001 viaf_485149294387580522619">خواجه احرار</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1010-item2">
                     <locus from="51r" to="56v">ff. 51r-56v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176974.0x000001 viaf_485149294387580522619">Aḥrār, ʿUbayd Allāh ibn Maḥmūd, 1403 or 1404-1489 or 1490</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_485149294387580522619">خواجه احرار</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_11389">Risālat vālidīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_11389">رسالة والديّه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Rare treatise on the tenets of the Naqshbandi school of Sufism by Sayyid Naṣīr al-Dīn ʿUbayd Allāh Aḥrār Ghijduvānī, known as Khvājah Aḥrār (d. 895/1490), conventionally thought to be lost, and later translated into Chaghatay Turkic by the Timurid or Mughal ruler, Emperor Ẓahīr al-Dīn Muḥammad Bābur (d. 937/1530). 
</p>
                        <p>The work was written at the request of the author’s father, hence the title. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                        <p>Oblique scribal shikastah āmīz continuing from folio 55 in rough Indian taʿlīq, probably by a different hand, similar to the replacement folio beginning item a.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
